Sasalin spewed a jet of flame, the tall Slakian igniting a small patch of forest before circling overhead, watching for the right moment. Strangely, when he slowed down, the eerie screeching behind him also stopped. Sasalin had forgotten that there was a passenger on his back.
"Come on, Tenruk, you've transformed into a Slakian before!"
"Flying on your own is completely different from being suddenly dragged away by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's okay, Kayer?"
Kayer clearly disagreed with Nishi's statement; he looked paler than usual, and his claws had dug deeply into Sasalin's back, drawing blood from the Slakian, but Sasalin obviously didn't care. That said, Sasalin realized he had scared his new friend and looked for an open area to land.
"Sorry, sorry, I caught a smell. I need to deal with it!"
"Do you have to drag us along too?" Tenook climbed down from Sasarin's back, sliding down the tail to the ground, and asked sharply. "We left Retvik behind! We abandoned that strong and quarrelsome big guy! How is he going to find us?"
"He'll figure it out..." Nishi nodded in agreement. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Can Retvik drive a car?"
Nishi blinked and turned to look at Tenook. "Of course he can drive a car."
"Have you ever seen Reitwick drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like yours. He only started taking the car to work because you always drove us. He only has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasalin suddenly burst out laughing, but no one knew what he found amusing. It took Sasalin a while before he calmed down.
"Sorry, sorry. I just imagined your big, armored friend riding a little bicycle designed for Temson children. That image is so ridiculous! I wish I had telepathy. That idea is so interesting! I definitely need to treasure it!"
Kayel also laughed, because he could imagine what Sasalin was thinking. "Alright, alright. But what did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?"
Sasalin hummed, quickly disappeared after taking off, and then flew back, dropping a corpse in front of Nishi. It was an Orosarak, a very rare golden-white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "Another one dead. I heard their screams. I smelled their blood. I must protect them, hunt down the killer. This is the will of Isini. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slak suddenly froze. Nisi and Kayer also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the open ground. A huge and pitch-black thing was staring at them, hissing. The creature suddenly spread its two pairs of massive wings and rushed forward, directly aiming at Sasalin, paying no heed to the three small figures standing in its way. Kayer and Tenuk barely dodged to the side, but Nisi found herself being dragged down and almost thrown onto Sasalin.
Sasalin grabbed Nisi by the arm, flung her onto his back with his long and nimble tail, and then took to the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly gave chase.
Kayer grumbled, drew his rifle from behind, and opened his bag to take out a bullet belt. He fastened the bullet belt around his chest for easy access, but quickly realized that Nisi, Sasalin, and the monster were no longer in sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Kayer asked.
"You want to go after them?"
"Nonsense."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? This rifle in my hand is powerful, and I can fire anytime. I just need to see it, and I can bring it down."
Tenook hesitated for a moment, then took a step back to give himself some space. With a low, slightly painful groan, Tenook's body stretched out, his fur turned into scales, and his arms turned into wings. He soon transformed into an ordinary pale blue Slak, but his eyes remained red.
"Come on up."
Tenuk now appears to be a fairly ordinary Slak, with neatly arranged scales on his back and a pair of sharp spines, making it easier for Kayel to grab him. It took Tenuk a long time to take flight, but once airborne, he quickly adjusted his direction, striving to catch up.
However, Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they were not facing only one opponent. A second dark monster surged up from beneath them, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid the collision.
"I guess this is the other terrifying monster that Ranex was worried about?" Kayel furrowed his brow, trying to shoot at the second monster but missing, then quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not respond; he was busy flying toward Nisi and Sasarin, despite the other monster chasing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to face the monster. The monster was in pursuit, which Kayel considered good news because it made aiming and shooting easier. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, causing it to howl in pain before disappearing into the forest. Kayel was unsure if it was still following them, but he felt it definitely couldn't keep up anymore.
Up ahead, Sasarin was frantically flailing his body, spewing flames at the black monster, while Nisi desperately held on to Sasarin to prevent himself from falling. Although this monster was certainly injured, it seemed enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs apparently hadn't caused too much damage. After Sasarin steadied himself, Nisi took the opportunity to pull out his weapon, a shotgun he trusted. Of course, a shotgun couldn't deal with such a monster, but the scattered bullets would at least scare off this black beast, right?
